'''''Studio Briefing''''' is an entertainment industry newsletter edited and published by [[Lew Irwin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hometown.aol.com/studiobrf/lewirwin/lewsbio.html|title=Lew Irwin's Web Page|accessdate=1 December 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060426210743/http://hometown.aol.com/studiobrf/lewirwin/lewsbio.html|archivedate=26 April 2006|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> ''Studio Briefing'' began "as a fax-only subscription service in 1992, [and] went online the following year".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://studiobriefing.net/studiobriefing.net/TV_News/Entries/2009/11/28_WE_HAVE_BEEN_DE-GOOGLED!.html|title=We have been de-Googled!|work=Studio Briefing|date=28 November 2009|accessdate=3 December 2009|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091202065803/http://www.studiobriefing.net/studiobriefing.net/TV_News/Entries/2009/11/28_WE_HAVE_BEEN_DE-GOOGLED!.html |archivedate=2 December 2009}}</ref> It had previously been syndicated through the Newshare corp.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newshare.com/Newshare/Syndicate/Topics/new.html#studio|title=What's new at Newshare/Clickshare?|work=Newshare|accessdate=3 December 2009}}</ref> It is currently available through the [[Internet Movie Database]].<ref>https://www.imdb.com/news/ns0000003/</ref> Studio Briefing also runs a blog at StudioBriefing.net.<ref>[http://www.studiobriefing.net Film and TV Industry News]</ref>
